@NODE INTRODUCTION "IndexGuide -- Introduction"
@NEXT DISTRIBUTION
@PREV MAIN
        @{b}IndexGuide V1.0@{ub}

        @{u}Introduction@{uu}


        IndexGuide is a little utility to make an index of all your
        guides and docs, and save it as a guide.

        Of course it is possible to make an index of other files, like pics
        or something similar. You just have to enter a pictureviewer instead
        of a textviewer.

        IndexGuide needs at least KICK 2.1 and @{"MUI 3.x" LINK "MUI"}.
        A better choise is KICK 3.x. With KICK < 3 there migth be some
        strange characters in the index.
@ENDNODE

@NODE DISTRIBUTION "IndexGuide -- Distribution"
@NEXT DISCLAIMER
@PREV INTRODUCTION
        @{b}IndexGuide V1.0@{ub}

        @{u}Distribution@{uu}


        You may spread IndexGuide, as long as you leave the contents
        of this archive intact, don`t add/remove/modify any file
        in this archive.
        The archive contains the following files:

        IndexGuide.info
        IndexGuide/IndexGuide
        IndexGuide/IndexGuide.info
        IndexGuide/IndexGuideDeu.guide
        IndexGuide/IndexGuideDeu.guide.info
        IndexGuide/IndexGuideEng.guide
        IndexGuide/IndexGuideEng.guide.info
        IndexGuide/Catalogs.info
        IndexGuide/Catalogs/deutsch.info
        IndexGuide/Catalogs/deutsch/IndexGuide.catalog

        IndexGuide is Mailware. If you use the programm, you should send @{"me" LINK "AUTHOR"}
        an e-mail or snail-mail. I would prefere a picturecard of your
        hometown. If you think, that is to much, it is ok and I will not
        be angy with you. :(
@ENDNODE

