@NODE USAGE "IndexGuide -- Usage"
@NEXT TOOLTYPES
@PREV INSTALLATION
        @{b}IndexGuide V1.0@{ub}

        @{u}Usage@{uu}


        The mainwindow (The Gadgets from top to bottom):
        @{b}Scan SourceDirs@{ub}
            The directories in the list below will be scanned.
            Another window will opened, where all files are listed,
            and the final index can be made.

        @{b}Directories to Scan@{ub}
            This list contains all directories, that IndexGuide will
            scan in order to make the index.

        @{b}Add Entry@{ub}
            Another directory can be added to the list above.

        @{b}Del Entry@{ub}
            The active Entry will be removed from the list.

        @{b}Clear List@{ub}
            All entries of the list will be removed.

        @{b}Pfad and Name of the Index@{ub}
            Here you must enter the path and name of the index.

        @{b}The Icon for the Guide@{ub}
            The index will get this icon.

        @{b}Default Tool@{ub}
            This will be the default tool of the index.

        @{b}Font for the index@{ub}
            This font will be used in the index. If no font is given, the
            systemdefault fon will be used.

        @{b}Viewer@{ub}
            Here you must enter a Viewer, which should be invoked
            to the display non #?.guide files. If you have docs in your
            guide, you should enter a textviewer. If you have pictures in
            you guide you would enter a pictureviewer.
            Important: You must enter the full path! Otherwise the links
            in the index will not work!
            (eg SYS:Utilities/Multivew)

        The Menu:
        Project
            @{b}About...@{ub}
                Displays an inforequester.
            @{b}About MUI...@{ub}
                Displays the AboutMUI.
            @{b}Quit@{ub}
                Quits IndexGuide.
        Settings
            @{b}MUI...@{ub}
                Invokes the MUI-Preferences-programm.
            @{b}Load Settings@{ub}
                Load the settings of IndexGuide from the @{"ToolTypes" LINK "TOOLTYPES"}.
            @{b}Save Settings@{ub}
                Save the settings of IndexGuide to the @{"ToolTypes" LINK "TOOLTYPES"}.

        The other window:

        This window opens after a klick on 'Scan SourceDirs'

        @{b}History@{ub}
            In this list IndexGuide informs the user about the
            current activity.

        @{b}Links in the Index@{ub}
            This list contains all files, that will be added to the
            index.

        @{b}Add Entry@{ub}
            Add another Entry to the right list.

        @{b}Del Entry@{ub}
            The active entry of the right list will be removed.

        @{b}Make the Index@{ub}
            The finel index will be created.
@ENDNODE

@NODE TOOLTYPES "IndexGuide -- ToolTypes"
@PREV USAGE
@NEXT HISTORY
        @{b}IndexGuide V1.0@{ub}

        @{u}ToolTypes@{uu}


        IndexGuide supports the following ToolTypes:

        @{b}GUIDE@{ub}
            Pfad/Name of the index.

        @{b}ICON@{ub}
            Icon for the index.

        @{b}DEFTOOL@{ub}
            DefaultTool for the index.

        @{b}VIEWER@{ub}
            Viewerprogramm for the file, which are no guides.
            Important: You must enter the full path!

        @{b}FONT@{ub}
            Font for the index. This tooltype must have the format
            <FONTNAME>/<SIZE>.

        @{b}SOURCEDIR@{ub}
            A Directory to scan.
            This tooltype may be used up to 100 times.
@ENDNODE

